MTN Nigeria Communications Plc (MTN) has completed the registration of 20,354,513,050 ordinary shares of N0.02 each with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). A statement from the telecommunication on Tuesday said the successful completion of the process sets in motion the next steps in the company’s intended listing by introduction on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE). Speaking on the announcement, the MTN CEO, Ferdi Moolman, said: “I am excited we have achieved another milestone in our listing process and want to thank the SEC and the Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC) for supporting us through the process. We have now begun to engage with the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) to complete the listing process.” B/ Haram: Buhari enlists UN support in rehabilitation of IDPs, destroyed infrastructure Nigeria galvanises global action for Northeast IDPs We’ll persuade  Boko Haram to let peace reign – Buhari Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin